==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leg bridge
<hw>Leg bridge</hw>. <def>A type of bridge for small spans in which the
floor girders are rigidly secured at their extremities to supporting
steel legs, driven into the ground as piling, or resting on
mudsills.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lege</ent>⟦br⟧
